cs.AR, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Audio and Speech Processing): The paper focuses on the application of Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) and presents an efficient RNN framework for FPGA implementations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with the design optimization of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), which are a type of machine learning model. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the implementation of RNNs on FPGA hardware, which involves software engineering aspects such as processing element design/optimization, quantization, activation implementation, etc. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper deals with the optimization of neural networks, specifically RNNs, for efficient hardware implementations. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper focuses on the implementation of RNNs on FPGA, which is a type of embedded system.
